result.execSummary:
The defendant Carson B Taylor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Court costs are due as follows:  $100.00 is due on or before 09/01/2022 and then $100.00 is due the first of each month thereafter until paid in full. A $15.00 payment plan fee has been added.  Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid and/or a civil judgment being entered for collection.

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen and report for booking. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.

records.addlTxt:
10:45 AM Defendant Carson B Taylor in court.  Attorney Crystal Leigh Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Carly June Sebion in court for Carson B Taylor. Defendant enters a plea of No Contest to Count 1. 3 tracking citations 22TR682, 683, 684  DRI. 
Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer contrary to 946.41(1). 

Joint recommendation: court costs only 

Court adopts the joint recommendation: Orders court costs only $443.00 pay at $100.00  month, first payment due on or before 9/1  pay each month thereafter until paid in full. FTP could result in commitment order to jail or civil judgment entered. 

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen and report for booking. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.
